Html is Hyper Text markup language
its basically make structure of a web page.

## creation of html:
in vs file you have to make the folder name index.html
index.html is the default home of every web page.

In html you have to use tag to do your work for example:

<p> hlw </p>
this is a tag of html name paragraph tag.
most of the tag are same like it.

Lets explore a basic html code, how a html code look like
you have to enter ! on vs code it will auto generate a code for you:
lets explain it now:

<!DOCTYPE html>                             // its tell the browser you are using html
<html lang="en">                             // form there html is started. its a opening of a tag ,its end in last
<head>                                      // in head tag you will tell some data ,but it will not appear on your browser
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Document</title>                    
</head>                                      // in there head is closed
<body>                                        // this is body opening and we will do everyting inside it.
  
</body>                                       
</html>                                // there html is closed

##lets write someting in html



<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Document</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>hemel</p>          // in there i create a paragraph tag and inside i wrote hemel
  </body>
</html>


